Did she leave her phone number?

113
00:07:57,640 --> 00:07:59,360
(Blood donator)

114
00:08:00,000 --> 00:08:00,920
When

115
00:08:01,320 --> 00:08:03,640
Xu Zhaolin took her to me,

116
00:08:04,280 --> 00:08:06,040
I found her familiar.

117
00:08:06,600 --> 00:08:08,040
After I thought hard,

118
00:08:08,760 --> 00:08:09,800
I finally remembered.

119
00:08:10,360 --> 00:08:12,040
I met her in the hospital.

120
00:08:14,000 --> 00:08:17,240
She risked her life on blood donation.

121
00:08:18,600 --> 00:08:19,280
Well,

122
00:08:20,320 --> 00:08:21,400
She has quite a hard life.

123
00:08:22,360 --> 00:08:22,920
You know what?

124
00:08:24,440 --> 00:08:25,400
She's an orphan.

125
00:08:33,680 --> 00:08:34,360
Orphan?

126
00:08:53,240 --> 00:08:55,640
You found no more clues
in the orphanage.

127
00:08:56,080 --> 00:08:57,200
But we're at least sure

128
00:08:57,480 --> 00:08:58,920
that you weren't discarded.

129
00:09:00,760 --> 00:09:01,240
Jia,

130
00:09:03,160 --> 00:09:05,120
I thought about it many times.

131
00:09:08,000 --> 00:09:10,320
If I were really discarded...

132
00:09:11,440 --> 00:09:12,120
Think about it.

133
00:09:13,240 --> 00:09:14,360
Even if I find them,

134
00:09:14,840 --> 00:09:16,080
how shall I face them?

135
00:09:16,920 --> 00:09:19,040
Don't overthink.

136
00:09:19,040 --> 00:09:20,200
You weren't discarded.

137
00:09:26,680 --> 00:09:28,080
But anyway,

138
00:09:28,440 --> 00:09:29,440
Xu Zhaolin

139
00:09:29,560 --> 00:09:31,480
